page.title: 11A CHILDS DAY
page.content: On Thursday I usually get up at 7 o'clock. I get washed, dressed, have breakfast, clean my teeth and leave for school at 9 o'clock. I walk to school which takes about 10 minutes. School begins at 9.25 am so I play with my friends and then we go in to school. We have an interval at 11.00 am which lasts for 20 minutes. After lunch at 12.30 pm we go out to play. I go home at 3.45 pm and then I go to Highland Dancing in Inverness. We do the Sword Dance, Reel and Highland Fling. I have been going to dancing for over a year. When I get home at 6 o'clock I have my supper and then I wash the dishes. If it is nice I go out to play with my friend Lucy. If not I watch T.V and go to bed at 10.30 pm. My favourite programme is 'Eastenders.'
